arch:property.oc:show_val: Rubble-built wall, 6.9 m long by .6 m wide by .66m high, and running obliquely from the southeast edge of the trench northwest to the second-to-last column of the center row, locus 11. Thus, it is essentially a continuation of the center n-s intercolumnar wall. It utilizes reused architectural elements and column drums (like the other intercolumnar walls), is built to incorporate the last column of the east row of the East Colonnade, and runs over/up to the east and center stylobates. The feature continues southeast to the so-called "Lower Market," joining an early terrace wall there. Built into this wall, face up, is the sculpted panel SF 60the bust of a male figure in low relief, missing its head.
